//
// T085 — `nsl-fmt --range LINE:LINE file.nsl` with a range that
// extends past the file's last line exits 2 with the frozen
// diagnostic from `formatting-rules.contract.md` §7 (and the
// matching exit-code matrix in `cli-surface.contract.md` §3).
//
// Frozen diagnostic:
//   error: --range <a>:<b> falls outside file (file has <N> lines)

// RUN: printf 'declare a { } module a { wire x[8]; }\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: not nsl-fmt --range 100:200 %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: error: --range 100:200 falls outside file (file has 1 lines)
